<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-05A3F26E-A144-4452-8888-E0A1BBEE8576" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-05A3F26E-A144-4452-8888-E0A1BBEE8576" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Smudge of all colors on edge of the print</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-50B00AD6-0A38-41AB-B3CF-DCE2951AFA8A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><table id="GUID-53E5F599-B620-44AD-919D-C7253ABD770C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Schematic overview 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Real example 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-EA4F42D3-7256-4353-A0AF-C24BFA702870" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-516FD356-B0F3-407D-AAEE-A24C08E65E40-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-516FD356-B0F3-407D-AAEE-A24C08E65E40-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-BAC1B9E4-B5CE-470E-981C-F5A13AD6C9F9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-613C5310-325B-4858-962A-C31AA10454D0-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-613C5310-325B-4858-962A-C31AA10454D0-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-EC1EAE23-40EC-4B10-A2C9-83873F76DC70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Symptoms</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Smudge of all colors on one spot 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The media is not flat on the surface 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> In some cases accompanied by ORE5709 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> In almost all cases the smudge is on the edge of the media (leading edge or side of media) 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-5F2114ED-D450-4262-8F28-0CEA4EC4D6BB" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Function Logging (if available)</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Media touch</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "> Printhead score</i> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The performance of the printheads is monitored in “Printhead Score”. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When score of different printheads start to fail in the same print this is an indication the media has touched the printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This can be seen if the X-scale is changed to “per engine_cycle_id” (See picture below). 
</p><fig id="GUID-2CFD939B-E619-4CD9-BE4E-4A129E819253" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CAFB8DD6-9652-487F-85A0-CA9B66FC93BD-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CAFB8DD6-9652-487F-85A0-CA9B66FC93BD-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> 
<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "> Nozzle performance</i> 
</p><fig id="GUID-7BE56B01-892B-4782-9210-8008671024A6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2ED4AF8D-9707-4314-9D89-9F2305FC594C-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2ED4AF8D-9707-4314-9D89-9F2305FC594C-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> A typical pattern of a media touch are multiple nozzle failures in the same swath over several printheads. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In the example above this happened 4 times during this print (swath 23, 65, 110 and 154). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">As mentioned above these touches didn't result in a permanent damage of the printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Media crash</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">A media crash will result in MRE5709. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This will abort the print and only the last swath of the print will show multiple failures. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case a printhead is permanently damaged due to a media touch/crash the “Printhead score” will permanently be decreased and also permanent failures are seen next prints in the “nozzle performance”. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-5259DD47-5351-40D5-A4C8-25BBBCE55314" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ADAM-triggers</title><p class="- topic/p ">No available ADAM-triggers 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><fig id="GUID-B10CAA56-0747-4EA3-817B-6FB3614E8C16" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7E866B29-DF94-4E5A-B1E1-E0AD8ABCDF33-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7E866B29-DF94-4E5A-B1E1-E0AD8ABCDF33-svg.svg"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-BB9BDDD1-E29C-42C5-BF10-2854E3AE4223" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Steps explanation</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-D963269B-E108-446A-A212-4581FEAA8740" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Type 
