</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Use another roll of the same media 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Cut the first 2 meters of the roll so the outside of the roll of media is scrapped 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check whether the platen is polluted 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Perform manual maintenance and clean platen 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check whether the settings in the profile are correct 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Vacuum settings 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Media thickness 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Print gap height 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">usage of Winder/ Tension bar 
</p></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Adjust profile 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The profile can be downloaded from: 
<xref href="https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check whether the media is Magnetic or static. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Install MOD39 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check whether the engine is level 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Level platen 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="ENGADJU01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-2BFE3033-C726-47A1-9A09-044CAA7F04FE.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 00 How to level the printer?>00 How to level the printer</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check the carriage height 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="03adju001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-5C85D6FC-5E14-4490-AB29-1EEC54BC3FB5.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 03 How to adjust the print height (calibration)?>03 How to adjust the print height (calibration)</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">15 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Adjust Carriage height 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="03adju001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-5C85D6FC-5E14-4490-AB29-1EEC54BC3FB5.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 03 How to adjust the print height (calibration)?>03 How to adjust the print height (calibration)</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">16 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether the X-tran rollers are clean 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">17 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Clean X-tran rollers 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">18 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check whether the X-tran rollers are damaged 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">19 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Repair broken X-tran rollers 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="15DISA001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D2422B11-B63C-4FEC-AA37-86683DEF45CA.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 15 How to remove the rollers of the Xtran pinch?>15 How to remove the rollers of the Xtran pinch</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">20 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check winder 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><draft-comment translate="no" class="- topic/draft-comment ">Link naar Winding of the media on the winder is not correct</draft-comment>
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-B389EE5D-1914-4E6C-B7F4-012907F4C808" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">To minimize the change of media touches/crashes the following topic should be taken care of: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Clean the platen on a regular basis. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Uses the correct profile when loading new media. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Make sure the edge of the media is not damaged. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Make sure the right media thickness is entered in the profile. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">When the media is not flat on the platen the printhead carriage can touch the surface of the media. In those cases the media wipes ink from printheads which will lead to local smudge on the media. Beware the printhead can also be damaged by a major media crash. In those cases permanent nozzle failures will be present.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The most important factor to keep the media flat on the platen is platen itself. There are ventilation holes on the platen which suck the media towards the platen. If this under pressure is not enough to pull the media down a change of media touch arises. The needed under pressure is defined in the media profile but heavily influenced by the condition of the media and the condition of the platen. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-945E6C60-1212-47DF-9487-92374227D4B4.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
